config HEARTBEAT_LED
    bool "Onboard LED heartbeat and key-activity indicator"
    default n
    help
      Blinks the onboard LED (led0 alias, GP25 on Raspberry Pi Pico) at 1 Hz
      as a power/heartbeat indicator, and briefly flashes it for 100 ms on
      every key-position change event as a proxy for UART data activity.

      The Raspberry Pi Pico has only a single green LED, so three distinct
      colours are not possible without additional hardware (e.g. an external
      WS2812 RGB LED).  Three states are indicated by different patterns:
        - 1 Hz blink          = board is powered and ZMK is running
        - 100 ms flash        = key event detected (UART TX/RX activity proxy)
        - LED off             = keyboard is in ZMK idle/sleep state

      Requires the target board to define a 'led0' GPIO alias.
